headlines.description: Hassani Gravett scored a lay-up, followed by a free throw with 6.5 seconds remaining to give South Carolina an 80-78 victory over Coastal Carolina in Colonial Life Arena on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gravett 3-point play lifts South Carolina to 80-78 victory

headlines.description: Torin Dorn had 22 points and a career-high 17 rebounds to help North Carolina State beat Missouri-Kansas City 88-69 on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dorn's double-double sends N.C. State past UMKC 88-69

headlines.description: Kevon Harris scored a career-high 31 points and Stephen F. Austin forced 27 turnovers to beat Rice 81-62 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris scores 31, leads Stephen F. Austin past Rice 81-62

headlines.description: Tony Carr scored 11 of his 19 points in the second half and Penn State beat George Washington 74-54 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Carr leads Penn State over George Washington

headlines.description: Max Strus scored a career-best 24 points and grabbed seven rebounds as DePaul beat Illinois-Chicago 65-55 on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Strus with 24 points leads DePaul over UIC 65-55

headlines.description: Otis Livingston II was 7-for-10 shooting and scored 17 points to help George Mason to a 77-65 win against North Carolina Central on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: George Mason uses balance to beat NC Central 77-65

headlines.description: Willie Rodriguez scored 22 points and Binghamton notched its sixth-straight win, beating Loyola (Maryland) 77-64 on Saturday afternoon.
Tookie Brown had 32 points, just two shy of his career high, to lead Georgia Southern to a 102-91 win over Savannah State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 32, Georgia Southern beats Savannah St. 102 91

headlines.description: Alan Herndon scored 21 points, Hayden Dalton got his second double-double of the season and Wyoming pulled away in the second half for an 86-72 win over Pacific on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wyoming pulls away from Pacific for 86-72 win

headlines.description: Jon Elmore scored 25 points, Ajdin Penava added 24 more and Marshall rallied late in the second half to slip past Toledo for a 93-87 win Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marshall slips past Toledo with late rally for 93-87 win

headlines.description: Jordan Geist, a role player known most for his scrappy style, scored 28 points Saturday night to help Missouri beat Green Bay 100-77.
headlines.shortLinkText: Geist leads Missouri past Green Bay 100-77

headlines.description: Khalil Ahmad ripped the nets for a career-high 34 points, burying 6 of 10 tries from 3-point range, and Cal State Fullerton held off Utah Valley 91-83 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ahmad scores 34 as CS Fullerton cools off Utah Valley 91-83

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
